works.description: It was earlier being speculated that Bernard Arnault’s LVMH, the French luxury goods conglomerate on an acquisition trail, was considering a bid for British luxury footwear firm Jimmy Choo. Now, the big news coming from the industry is that the luxury goods group Labelux from TowerBrook Capital Partners LP has bought the fashionistas’ favorite shoemaker. The terms of the deal haven’t been revealed, but two familiar sources said it was worth about £500 million (over $809 million).
